  "read": [
    "EP8 smooths local routed expert VJP GEMM slightly versus EP4, but the backward dX combine grows sharply and becomes the largest MoE-specific wall.",
    "The big anonymous GEMM bucket is not only routed MoE. Shared expert dense backward is about 1.93-1.97 s/rank/step and remains essentially unchanged between EP4 and EP8.",
    "Attention kernels are stable at about 2.07 s/rank/step across EP4 and EP8 in this guarded/shared-KV prototype path: forward attention plus dK/dV plus dQ.",
    "Pure Triton SwiGLU is now second-order at about 0.10-0.12 s/rank/step after the runtime-n_elements patch.",
    "Next ladder: reduce MORI backward combine_dx, then replace padded owner-rank VJP GEMM family with fused or grouped training GEMM, while keeping shared expert dense backward and attention kernels as separate buckets."
  ]
